This project aims to provide a custom welcome voice greeting to the user after logging into the system.

Steps to be followed:

->Ubuntu 14.04 LTS:
	1. Change the path in the file 'greeting_runfile.sh' to '/path/to/runfile.sh/in/your/system/'
	2. Similarly, change the paths in 'runfile.sh' to '/path/to/the/corresponding/file/in/your/system/'
	3. Copy the file 'greeting_runfile.sh' in '/etc/profile.d/' (You may need root priviledges).
	
To customize the greeting message:

	1. Edit the corresponding lines of the file 'greeting_variety'.
	2. Save the file.
	3. Changes will take effect after logging off.
